ably, the\ndistance of the receiver (or source) from the lensing object greatly influences\nthe deflection angle. Moreover, $c_{\\rm O}$ needs be negative for a consistent\nsolution. In our analysis, the rotating black hole acts as a particle\naccelerator and possesses the sensitivity to probe the symmergent gravity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Aug 2022 03:41:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Oct 2022 13:10:28 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 26 Mar 2023 09:46:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-28"}
