ent computational models for the interaction of arbitrarily curved\nfibers, such that the disk represents the cross-section of the first and the\ncylinder a local approximation to the shape of the second fiber.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Aug 2022 10:00:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Aug 2022 07:37:04 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 18 Aug 2022 14:06:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-19"}
